Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
2 Glen Street is right on the harbors edge with exceptional views over the harbor allowing ample natural light through the floor to ceiling windows.  The suite is fitted out with a boardroom, office and open plan area.

This is an opportunity not to be missed.

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to offer for sale Suite 802, 68 Alfred Street, Milsons Point. Positioned on the eighth floor, the suite has captivating harbour views from the expansive north easterly aspect.

Suite 802, 68 Alfred Street benefits from the following key investment highlights:

• Month to month lease, ideal for investors or owner occupiers
• Captivating Sydney Harbour views from an elevated eighth-floor position
• Large 172sqm* half floor office 
• secure basement car space
• Modern fitout equipped with 8 offices, kitchenette, boardroom, storage / printer room and reception area
• Located opposite Milson’s Point Train Station, Kirribilli Village shops and 300m* from Kirribilli Ferry Wharf

The property will be offered for sale by Public Auction on Tuesday 17th of April 2018 at 10.30am at AuctionWORKS, Mezzanine Level, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney.

For further information, please contact the exclusive selling agents:

Jason Lowry - 0419 277 527
Toby Silk - 0422 143 813

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: OFFICE SUITE WITH CAPTIVATING HARBOUR VIEWS

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Would Sit Retail or Commercial Uses

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the heart of Milsons Point, at the base of a residential tower and only minutes to the train station, this well-presented retail shop would suit a myriad of uses. 

* 82sqm internally
* 50sqm private, exclusive use courtyard at the rear
* Two cars spaces in tandem
* Nearly 6m of floor to ceiling glass shopfront
* Current fit out may remain (if required) including floating timber floors, ceiling plus downlights, male & female toilets, sinks and benches
* Ducted air conditioning throughout
* Glass sliding doors at the rear opening onto the exclusive use courtyard
* Potential for external seating at the front of the tenancy (STCA)
* Kitchen equipment available for purchase (if required) including fridges, dishwasher, benches, display cabinets and coffee machine
* Street parking directly in front and opposite
* Surrounded by soaring residential towers and metres to numerous commercial offices, the strip is supported by leading retailers QE Foodstores, Le Pont Wine Store, Milsons Point Medical Centre plus an abundance of cafes & eateries 

Currently trading as a high end cake shop, the premises would suit retail, beauty, medical, office or a food & beverage operator requiring minimal cooking. 

For more information or to arrange an inspection, please contact Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BEAUTIFULLY PRESENTED RETAIL WITH PRIVATE COURTYARD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located on the south side of Lavender Street at the corner of Cliff Street and is within easy walking distance of both Milsons Point and North Sydney railway stations.

A 19-storey office block with 2 levels of parking for 110 cars. The building was fully upgraded in 1996, involving the refurbishment of the foyer and facade, provision of floor by floor air-conditioning and modernisation of the lifts.

Suite 201 has a fit out in place of open plan area, five offices, boardroom, comms room, and kitchenette; furniture can also be included.  There is also a tandem car space for 2 cars.

For further details or to arrange an inspection please contact Michael or Lisa on 9954 3333.
